Steps to follow after installing all dependencies,

1)clone repository in local pc 
2)Open project in vs code or any editor
3)change directory to \backend ,install -r requirements.txt in terminal
4)change .env file  DATABASE_URL = Postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@127.0.0.1:5432/employee_management (mentioned in readme file also)
and also change config.py with your respective postgres password.
5)run --> .\run_postgres_setup.bat
6)python app.py
7)Terminal asks database password: enter you database password
8)open 1 more terminal cd to \frontend 
9)run this command in terminal so that it will allow installing npm: Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process.
10)run commands, npm install ,npm run dev
11)Your application is up and running (http://localhost:5177/) !!!!


You can view complete video of app by downloading EmployeeprojectVideoofapp.zip file.


Thank You
